act.article:
    2 Definitions.—In 
    these rules, unless the context otherwise requires,—  




    a    “Act” means the Repatriation of Prisoners Act, 2003 (49 of 2003);  




    b    “application” means an application made under section 4 of the Act;  




    c    “diplomatic channel” means through the missions of the respective 
    countries;  




    d    “section” means a section of the Act;  




    e    all other words and expressions used in these rules and not defined 
    but defined in the Act shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them 
    in that Act.
